Nadal Defeats Murray to Join Djokovic in U.S. Tennis Open Men’s Final

-- B y   R o b   G l o s t e r
-- 
2011-09-11T01:10:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-11/nadal-defeats-murray-to-join-djokovic-in-u-s-tennis-open-men-s-final.html
Defending champion  Rafael Nadal  of
Spain defeated  Andy Murray , the fourth seed from Britain, in
four sets tonight to reach the U.S. Open men’s final.  Nadal, seeded second, won 6-4, 6-2, 3-6, 6-2 and will face
top seed Novak Djokovic of  Serbia  in the final. It will be a
rematch of last year’s finalists.  Djokovic earlier recovered from a two-set deficit to defeat
five-time champion  Roger Federer  in their semifinal.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Rob Gloster at 
 rgloster@bloomberg.net  